"{\"uid\": \"catholicnewsagency.com-news-258450-muslim-leaders-condemn-disgraceful-olympics-scene-it-offended-us-as-much-as-them\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"ByKate Qui\\u00f1ones  CNA Staff, Jul 30, 2024 /             16:22 pm  Top government officials in Iran and Turkey, along with other Muslim religious figures, are speaking out against the drag-queen-led parody of the Last Supper at the Paris Olympics opening ceremony that shocked Christians and others across the world.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 314, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 17, \"end\": 20, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Copy_number_variation\", \"score\": 0.9949115911413619, \"rank\": 0.002955236811341704, \"text\": \"CNA\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Copy_number_variation\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Copy_number_variation\"}, {\"begin\": 93, \"end\": 97, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Iran\", \"score\": 0.8817525979125805, \"rank\": 0.13396685735403732, \"text\": \"Iran\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Iran\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Iran\"}, {\"begin\": 102, \"end\": 108, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Turkey\", \"score\": 0.9994439311071586, \"rank\": 0.000556378253622027, \"text\": \"Turkey\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Turkey\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Turkey\"}, {\"begin\": 127, \"end\": 133, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Islam\", \"score\": 0.999968363812726, \"rank\": 3.163718788210709e-05, \"text\": \"Muslim\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Islam\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Islam\"}, {\"begin\": 275, \"end\": 285, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christians\", \"score\": 0.685813581034886, \"rank\": 0.4485856167636144, \"text\": \"Christians\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christians\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christians\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The supreme leader of Iran, Ayatollah Ali Khamenei, condemned the \\\"insults\\\" against Jesus Christ, noting that Jesus is a respected figure in Islam.\", \"from\": 316, \"to\": 463, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 338, \"end\": 342, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Iran\", \"score\": 0.8817525979125805, \"rank\": 0.13396685735403732, \"text\": \"Iran\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Iran\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Iran\"}, {\"begin\": 344, \"end\": 366, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ali_Khamenei\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Ayatollah Ali Khamenei\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ali_Khamenei\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ali_Khamenei\"}, {\"begin\": 354, \"end\": 366, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ali_Khamenei\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.476617562325251e-14, \"text\": \"Ali Khamenei\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ali_Khamenei\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ali_Khamenei\"}, {\"begin\": 400, \"end\": 412, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus_in_Christianity\", \"score\": 0.96178058288507, \"rank\": 0.039738156669692916, \"text\": \"Jesus Christ\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus_in_Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus_in_Christianity\"}, {\"begin\": 426, \"end\": 431, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus_in_Christianity\", \"score\": 0.9735934614573838, \"rank\": 0.02712202814427741, \"text\": \"Jesus\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus_in_Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus_in_Christianity\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Respect for #JesusChrist \\u2026 is an indisputable, definite matter for Muslims,\\\" Khamenei said in apost on X.\", \"from\": 465, \"to\": 571, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 533, \"end\": 540, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Islam\", \"score\": 0.9999718477631325, \"rank\": 2.8149634441501807e-05, \"text\": \"Muslims\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Islam\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Islam\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We condemn these insults directed at the holy figures of divine religions, including Jesus Christ,\\\" added the supreme leader of Iran since 1989.\", \"from\": 572, \"to\": 717, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 658, \"end\": 670, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus_in_Christianity\", \"score\": 0.96178058288507, \"rank\": 0.039738156669692916, \"text\": \"Jesus Christ\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus_in_Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus_in_Christianity\"}, {\"begin\": 701, \"end\": 705, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Iran\", \"score\": 0.8817525979125805, \"rank\": 0.13396685735403732, \"text\": \"Iran\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Iran\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Iran\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Turkish President Recep Tayyi Erdo\\u011fan also spoke out against the ceremony, saying he intended to call Pope Francis at the earliest opportunity to discuss the \\\"immorality committed against the Christian world.\\\"\", \"from\": 719, \"to\": 928, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 719, \"end\": 736, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/President_of_Turkey\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Turkish President\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/President_of_Turkey\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/President_of_Turkey\"}, {\"begin\": 749, \"end\": 756, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Recep_Tayyip_Erdo\\u011fan\", \"score\": 0.9996948278673649, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Erdo\\u011fan\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Recep_Tayyip_Erdo\\u011fan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Recep_Tayyip_Erdo\\u011fan\"}, {\"begin\": 821, \"end\": 833, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pope_Francis\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Pope Francis\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19546\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pope_Francis\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pope_Francis\"}, {\"begin\": 911, \"end\": 920, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.8665959262863769, \"rank\": 0.153940342513787, \"text\": \"Christian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The \\\"disgraceful scene in Paris offended not only the Catholic world, not only the Christian world, but also us as much as them,\\\" Erdo\\u011fan said during\\u00a0anaddressin the country's capital of Ankara.\", \"from\": 930, \"to\": 1124, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 956, \"end\": 961, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999781468368798, \"rank\": 2.185364087970948e-05, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 984, \"end\": 992, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\", \"score\": 0.9999999998749445, \"rank\": 8.18431674960888e-11, \"text\": \"Catholic\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\"}, {\"begin\": 1013, \"end\": 1022, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.8665959262863769, \"rank\": 0.153940342513787, \"text\": \"Christian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}, {\"begin\": 1060, \"end\": 1067, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Recep_Tayyip_Erdo\\u011fan\", \"score\": 0.9996948278673649, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Erdo\\u011fan\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Recep_Tayyip_Erdo\\u011fan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Recep_Tayyip_Erdo\\u011fan\"}, {\"begin\": 1117, \"end\": 1123, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ankara\", \"score\": 0.9350487541528346, \"rank\": 0.06946133945624777, \"text\": \"Ankara\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ankara\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ankara\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Immorality displayed at the opening of the Paris Olympics once again highlighted the scale of the threat we face,\\\" he added.\", \"from\": 1126, \"to\": 1251, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Muslims do not recognize the divinity of Jesus but do reverence him as a prophet.\", \"from\": 1253, \"to\": 1334, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1253, \"end\": 1260, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Islam\", \"score\": 0.9999718477631325, \"rank\": 2.8149634441501807e-05, \"text\": \"Muslims\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Islam\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Islam\"}, {\"begin\": 1294, \"end\": 1299, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus_in_Christianity\", \"score\": 0.9735934614573838, \"rank\": 0.02712202814427741, \"text\": \"Jesus\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus_in_Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus_in_Christianity\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The top institution of the Sunni branch of Islam in Egypt also issued astatementcondemning the Olympic ceremony portrayal.\", \"from\": 1336, \"to\": 1458, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1363, \"end\": 1368, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sunni_Islam\", \"score\": 0.9999991303192617, \"rank\": 8.696816949130021e-07, \"text\": \"Sunni\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sunni_Islam\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sunni_Islam\"}, {\"begin\": 1388, \"end\": 1393, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Egypt\", \"score\": 0.9999998231965194, \"rank\": 1.5990983950680817e-07, \"text\": \"Egypt\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Egypt\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Egypt\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The scenes portray Jesus \\u200eChrist,\\\" the Al-Azhar statement read, \\\"in an offensive image that involves disrespect to his person.\\\"\", \"from\": 1460, \"to\": 1588, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1480, \"end\": 1485, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus_in_Christianity\", \"score\": 0.9735934614573838, \"rank\": 0.02712202814427741, \"text\": \"Jesus\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus_in_Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus_in_Christianity\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Al-Azhar, and nearly 2 billion Muslims behind it, believe that Jesus \\u2026 is the \\u200eMessenger of Allah.\", \"from\": 1590, \"to\": 1689, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1622, \"end\": 1629, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Islam\", \"score\": 0.9999718477631325, \"rank\": 2.8149634441501807e-05, \"text\": \"Muslims\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Islam\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Islam\"}, {\"begin\": 1654, \"end\": 1659, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus_in_Christianity\", \"score\": 0.9735934614573838, \"rank\": 0.02712202814427741, \"text\": \"Jesus\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus_in_Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus_in_Christianity\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Quran reads, Jesus is Allah's 'Word through Mary and a spirit \\u200efrom him.'\\\"\", \"from\": 1690, \"to\": 1768, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1694, \"end\": 1699, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Quran\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.913808074664272e-33, \"text\": \"Quran\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Quran\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Quran\"}, {\"begin\": 1707, \"end\": 1712, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus_in_Christianity\", \"score\": 0.9735934614573838, \"rank\": 0.02712202814427741, \"text\": \"Jesus\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus_in_Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus_in_Christianity\"}, {\"begin\": 1738, \"end\": 1742, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mary_in_Islam\", \"score\": 0.9999999988267518, \"rank\": 1.17261213244055e-09, \"text\": \"Mary\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q2566598\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mary_in_Islam\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mary_in_Islam\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Muslim Council of Elders, under the chairmanship of Dr. Ahmed Al-Tayeb, the grand imam of Al-Azhar, also issued adenunciationof the opening ceremony.\", \"from\": 1770, \"to\": 1923, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"This disgraceful act showed a complete lack of respect for the beliefs of religious people and the high moral values they hold dear,\\\" the statement read.\", \"from\": 1925, \"to\": 2079, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The council unequivocally rejects all attempts to demean religious symbols, beliefs, and sacred figures.\\\"\", \"from\": 2080, \"to\": 2186, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Christian as well as other leadersworldwide have spoken out against Friday's opening ceremonies of the 2024 Paris Olympics.\", \"from\": 2188, \"to\": 2311, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The world's wealthiest individual, Elon Musk,calledthe scene \\\"extremely disrespectful to Christians.\\\"\", \"from\": 2312, \"to\": 2413, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2347, \"end\": 2356, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Elon_Musk\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Elon Musk\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Elon_Musk\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Elon_Musk\"}, {\"begin\": 2401, \"end\": 2411, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christians\", \"score\": 0.685813581034886, \"rank\": 0.4485856167636144, \"text\": \"Christians\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christians\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christians\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The controversialshow, part of the 1.5-billion-euro (about $1.62 billion) spectacle to kick off the Olympic Games, featured drag queens portraying the apostles and an overweight DJ as Jesus in what appeared to be part of a fashion show apparently mocking Leonardo da Vinci's famous painting of the Last Supper.\", \"from\": 2415, \"to\": 2725, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2599, \"end\": 2604, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus_in_Christianity\", \"score\": 0.9735934614573838, \"rank\": 0.02712202814427741, \"text\": \"Jesus\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus_in_Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus_in_Christianity\"}, {\"begin\": 2670, \"end\": 2687, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leonardo_da_Vinci\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.159315084900149e-21, \"text\": \"Leonardo da Vinci\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leonardo_da_Vinci\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leonardo_da_Vinci\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Anne Descamps, spokesperson for the Paris Olympics, defended the opening ceremonies,saying\\\"there was never an intention to show disrespect to any religious group.\\\"\", \"from\": 2727, \"to\": 2890, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2732, \"end\": 2740, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jean-Baptiste_Descamps\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Descamps\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jean-Baptiste_Descamps\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jean-Baptiste_Descamps\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She said the goal of the opening ceremony was to \\\"celebrate community tolerance.\\\"\", \"from\": 2892, \"to\": 2973, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"(Story continues below)  \\\"We believe this ambition was achieved.\", \"from\": 2975, \"to\": 3039, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"If people have taken any offense we are really sorry,\\\" Descamps added.\", \"from\": 3040, \"to\": 3110, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3095, \"end\": 3103, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jean-Baptiste_Descamps\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Descamps\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jean-Baptiste_Descamps\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jean-Baptiste_Descamps\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Bishop Robert BarronpannedDescamps' statement as \\\"anything but an apology.\\\"\", \"from\": 3112, \"to\": 3187, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Your monthly donation will help our team continue reporting the truth, with fairness, integrity, and fidelity to Jesus Christ and his Church.\", \"from\": 3189, \"to\": 3330, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3302, \"end\": 3314, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus_in_Christianity\", \"score\": 0.96178058288507, \"rank\": 0.039738156669692916, \"text\": \"Jesus Christ\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus_in_Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus_in_Christianity\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Father Jason Nioka's first assignment as a priest is to spend his summer in Paris in charge of the Catholic chaplains serving the Olympic athletes in Paris.\", \"from\": 3332, \"to\": 3488, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3339, \"end\": 3344, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jason\", \"score\": 0.9874631208184727, \"rank\": 0.01269497112721794, \"text\": \"Jason\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jason\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jason\"}, {\"begin\": 3408, \"end\": 3413, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999781468368798, \"rank\": 2.185364087970948e-05, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 3431, \"end\": 3439, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\", \"score\": 0.9999999998749445, \"rank\": 8.18431674960888e-11, \"text\": \"Catholic\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\"}, {\"begin\": 3482, \"end\": 3487, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999781468368798, \"rank\": 2.185364087970948e-05, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Among the chaplains, 40 Catholic priests, nuns, and laypeople are catering to the spiritual needs of the Olympic athletes in the Multifaith Center.\", \"from\": 3490, \"to\": 3637, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3514, \"end\": 3522, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\", \"score\": 0.9999999998749445, \"rank\": 8.18431674960888e-11, \"text\": \"Catholic\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The ceremony drew criticism around the world for its profane depiction of the Last Supper.\", \"from\": 3639, \"to\": 3729, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"CNA is a service ofEWTN News, Inc.\", \"from\": 3731, \"to\": 3765, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3731, \"end\": 3734, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Copy_number_variation\", \"score\": 0.9949115911413619, \"rank\": 0.002955236811341704, \"text\": \"CNA\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Copy_number_variation\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.or